		at the end of its design lifetime from the end of 2018, there is a 64% chance that peak global mean temperature 
		rise remains below 1.5 °C. Delaying mitigation until 2030 considerably reduces the likelihood that 1.5 °C would be 
		attainable even if the rate of fossil fuel retirement was accelerated. Although the challenges laid out by the Paris 
